{"questionId":"19686","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The following diagram shows a circle with centre <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>O</mtext></math> and radius <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/a29badcb3ec6a7d75f0e46a87043718ccb1d2f25.png\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">Points <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>B</mtext></math> lie on the circumference of the circle.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">Chord <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mtext>AB</mtext></mfenced></math>&nbsp;has length <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext><mover><mtext>O</mtext><mo>^</mo></mover><mtext>B</mtext><mo>=</mo><mi>θ</mi></math>&nbsp;radians.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Show that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>18</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>18</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></msqrt></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>uses the cosine rule &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>(M1)</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>L</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mn>3</mn></mfenced><mfenced><mn>3</mn></mfenced><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>A1</strong></p>\n<p>so&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>18</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>18</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></msqrt></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>AG</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>[2 marks]</strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"19686","referenceCode":"EXN.2.SL.TZ0.2b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Show that L=18-18 cos θ.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.2—2d and 3d trig, sine rule, cosine rule, area","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.4—Circle: radians, arcs, sectors"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}